Reasoning: The paper deals with channel estimation and compensation of nonlinear distortion in OFDM communication systems, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of a decision-aided algorithm for adaptive compensation suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The computer simulation aspect of the paper may also make it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
